# Dogfood-agent throwaway vault + config (personal, never ships).
# The .example template IS committed so public users can bootstrap a
# parallel daemon on :9001 from a fresh clone. `dogfood/*` (not `dogfood/`)
# is required so the negation below can re-include a single file — git
# won't descend into a directory wholly ignored by the directory form.
dogfood/*
!dogfood/emptyos.toml.example

# Personal apps & engines (not shipped with core OS)
apps/personal/
engines/personal/
tests/personal/

# Personal skills (contain PII — names, paths, career data)
